課程概述 Course Description
       從災害發生次數與影響人數來看，颱洪災害每年均造成一定的財產損失與傷亡。因此透過災害防救體系的運作與科技的協助，來說明如何減少颱洪災害的損失。進而藉由災例分析，來探討颱洪災害對社會不同面向的影響。同時，也討論氣候變遷對颱洪災害強度的影響。Based on number of events and affected population, hydro-metrological hazards bring property losses and casualties each year. In order to explain measures to mitigate adverse impacts, operational framework of disaster management and assistance of science & technology will help to identify focal issues to discuss. Furthermore, case studies will illustrate multi-dimensional considerations of typhoons, floods and torrential rainfalls. For providing broader viewpoints, climate change will be addressed to cover future impacts.    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    Through in-class introduction and discussions to give a comprehensive understanding of measures is given to mitigate impacts brought by typhoons and torrential rainfalls. Learning from past events and future prospects of international development will provide an evidence-based investigation to build up capability of disaster risk reduction on hydro-metrological hazards.    

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1Introduction physical and social impacts brought by Hydro-Meteorological Hazards2The framework and operation of disaster management system in Taiwan (1) central government level3The framework and operation of disaster management system in Taiwan (2) local government level4The framework and operation of disaster management system in Taiwan (3) community level5International evolution and tendency on hazard mitigation6Case study 1- an extremely typhoon event, Typhoon Morakot, to illustrate importance of scientific-based operation7Future threat climate change, through introducing Taiwan’s effort to explain how possible impacts could influence Taiwan8Water resource management and drought to address how to reach a balance between economic development, people’s livelihoods and agricultural industry9Briefing on comprehensive river basin management to provide an integrated solution of flood control10Introduction of loss assessment of food which will support decision making11Topics on social vulnerability to explore diverse aspects of flood impacts12Case study 2 – events of torrential-rainfall-triggered geo-hazards to explain compound-type disaster bring cascading impacts13Hydro-meteorological-induced hazards to demonstrate the hardware construction to mitigate slopeland failure and debris flow which are major induced hazards14Hydro-meteorological-induced hazards to demonstrate the software measures to mitigate slopeland failure and debris flow which are major induced hazards15On-hand exercise on using geo-spatial tools to produce hazard maps16Group presentation17Group presentation18Final examination 

　以上每週進度教師可依上課情況做適度調整。The schedule may be subject to change.


